From: Mike Soultanian <msoultan(-at-)csulb.edu>

I would take off your entire clutch/flywheel assembly and bring it to a 
machine shop.  Have them check it out to make sure it's within spec, 
then have them balance it (clutch/pressure plate, too).  It might be 
badly out of balance causing excess vibration.

Jamey Charlet wrote:

> Hi Volks ~~~
> I've had the misfortune to find that the rattle I hear upon start up is not
> the engine tin --- it's the loose flywheel. Apparently the PO didn't tighten
> things properly when he changed the clutch before I bought Slo Rojo (lesson:
> get a torque wrench), and now it seems that I can't tighten it enough to
> prevent rattling.


